      "content": "i see. so if we're being completely realistic about how the world works, even in academia, isn't it true that the \"standard\" version is objectively better for communicating complex ideas? like, if a scholar used the style in Text B, wouldn't they be seen as less capable of handling rigorous, high-level research compared to someone who uses the vocabulary in Text A? wouldn't that mean the dialect itself is a marker for a different level of intellectual depth?",
